Definition: a highly publicized trial in 1925 when John Thomas Scopes violated a Tennessee state law by teaching evolution in high school
Example: Scopes was prosecuted by William Jennings Bryan and defended by Clarence Darrow; Scopes was convicted but the verdict was later reversed
Synonyms: trial, noun, group, law, c, process, evolution, a, highly, publicized, in, when, John, Thomas, Scopes, violated, Tennessee, state, by, teaching, high, school, was, prosecuted, William, Jennings, Bryan, and, defended, Clarence, Darrow, convicted, but, the, verdict, later, reversed
Category: noun.act
